M6 — OFFSET vs keyset pagination over transaction (5,000,000 rows)
Both queries at the same logical position: row 500,001 onward, LIMIT 50.
No new index — both plans use the existing transaction_pkey (PK on id).

=== OFFSET: SELECT * FROM transaction ORDER BY id LIMIT 50 OFFSET 500000; ===
--- cold ---
 Limit  (cost=17468.43..17470.18 rows=50 width=40) (actual time=129.492..129.507 rows=50 loops=1)
   Buffers: shared hit=7163
   ->  Index Scan using transaction_pkey on transaction  (cost=0.43..174680.43 rows=5000000 width=40) (actual time=0.106..100.440 rows=500050 loops=1)
         Buffers: shared hit=7163
 Planning:
   Buffers: shared hit=96
 Planning Time: 0.678 ms
 Execution Time: 129.655 ms

